# Create Binary Tree From Descriptions (LeetCode 2196)

## 📌 Problem Statement

You are given a 2D integer array `descriptions` where:

* `descriptions[i] = [parent, child, isLeft]`
* `parent` is the value of a parent node.
* `child` is the value of a child node.
* `isLeft` indicates whether the child is a left child (`1`) or a right child (`0`).

Construct and return the root of the binary tree described by `descriptions`.

It is guaranteed that the given descriptions form a valid binary tree.

---

## 🧠 Approach

### 1. Create Nodes Dynamically

Use a hash map (`unordered_map<int, TreeNode*>`) to store all nodes.

For every description:

* If the parent node does not exist, create it.
* If the child node does not exist, create it.

This ensures each value corresponds to exactly one `TreeNode`.

### 2. Connect Parent and Child

Based on the value of `isLeft`:

* `1` → attach the child as the left child.
* `0` → attach the child as the right child.

### 3. Identify the Root

A root node is the only node that never appears as a child.

Use another hash map to track:

* Parent nodes → mark as potential roots.
* Child nodes → mark as non-roots.

After processing all descriptions, the node marked as a parent but never as a child is the root.

### 4. Return the Root Node

Retrieve the root value and return the corresponding node from the node map.

---

## 💻 Code (C++)

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* createBinaryTree(vector<vector<int>>& descriptions) {
        unordered_map<int, TreeNode*> mp;
        unordered_map<int, int> root;

        for (int i = 0; i < descriptions.size(); i++) {

            if (mp[descriptions[i][0]] == 0) {
                TreeNode* temp = new TreeNode(descriptions[i][0]);
                mp[descriptions[i][0]] = temp;
            }

            if (mp[descriptions[i][1]] == 0) {
                TreeNode* temp = new TreeNode(descriptions[i][1]);
                mp[descriptions[i][1]] = temp;
            }

            if (descriptions[i][2] == 1) {
                mp[descriptions[i][0]]->left = mp[descriptions[i][1]];
            } else {
                mp[descriptions[i][0]]->right = mp[descriptions[i][1]];
            }

            if (root[descriptions[i][0]] != -1) {
                root[descriptions[i][0]] = 1;
            }

            root[descriptions[i][1]] = -1;
        }

        int value = 0;

        for (auto &it : root) {
            if (it.second == 1) {
                value = it.first;
                break;
            }
        }

        return mp[value];
    }
};
```

---

## 🚀 Example

### Input

```text
descriptions = [[20,15,1],[20,17,0],[50,20,1],[50,80,0],[80,19,1]]
```

### Constructed Tree

```text
        50
       /  \
      20   80
     / \   /
    15 17 19
```

### Output

```text
[50,20,80,15,17,19]
```

